                        textEn: "In the year 622 CE, tension peaked in the alleyways of Mecca as an assassination plot against the Prophet was set in motion. Yet, that night became the dawn of the most decisive maneuver in history: the Hijrah. Armed with brilliant strategy, Prophet Muhammad and Abu Bakr slipped away, taking refuge within the miraculous spider's web of the Cave of Thawr, before braving the unforgiving desert toward Medina. Those sacrifices and tears found their ultimate answer eight years later. Accompanied by 10,000 Muslims, the Prophet marched back into Mecca. The ancient world, accustomed to bloody conquests, stood stunned; instead of unsheathing swords of vengeance, he bowed his head and proclaimed a mass amnesty. Mecca was liberated without a single drop of blood shed. The idols surrounding the Kaaba were dismantled as the words echoed, 'The truth has come, and falsehood has vanished,' restoring the sanctuary as the spiritual axis of the world.",
